Luis Suarez has been welcomed back to training with the rest of the Barcelona squad. Suarez, who was not involved in the friendly against Nastic, trained on Monday afternoon with his team-mates. Sport reports that Suarez completed the session like anyone else by doing all the exercises and working despite his row with the club on ending his contract. Barca had threatened that he will sit in the stand for one-year if he fails to agree on the exit plan, as they want him to walk without paying for his final year deal. Suarez is in contact with Juventus and Atletico Madrid about a move-away. 